At the 2022 G20 Summit in Bali, President Biden, Indonesian President Widodo, and European Commission President Von der Leyen co-hosted a group of G20 leaders to demonstrate their commitment to the Partnership for Global Infrastructure and Investment (PGII). The aim of the PGII is to accelerate investment in quality infrastructure in low- and middle-income countries and strengthen the global economy. The leaders highlighted the collaboration and support among like-minded partners and showcased how PGII partners are financing transformative infrastructure projects and mobilizing the private sector. President Biden announced new projects and provided updates on the progress and impact of PGII. These initiatives are in line with the G20 theme for 2022, "Recover Together, Recover Stronger," and aim to create lasting positive impacts, strengthen community resilience, and support inclusive and sustainable development.